    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. but if the original meaning of the text is so hard to prove—since people had different intentions—doesn't that make the whole thing feel a bit arbitrary? like, isn't it just a way to give judges more freedom to pick whatever they want as long as they claim it's \"original\"?",
